    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my blueberry bushes are turning kind of yellow on the leaves. i cant tell if they need more nitrogen or if the soil pH is just messed up. any idea how to tell the difference?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on blueberry bushes can be caused by several things, but it's often related to nutrient deficiencies or soil issues. If the yellowing appears uniformly across older leaves, it might point toward a nitrogen deficiency. However, if the yellowing is interveinal (yellow between the veins) and the soil pH is outside the optimal range for blueberries, that could be the culprit. You can test your soil pH to get a definitive answer about acidity, which is crucial for blueberries.",
      "source": "target",
